ngs":["English, Scottish, and Irish: variant of   Gray  .","German: dialect variant of   Grau  .","In some cases also an American shortened and altered form of Ukrainian <b>Grushko</b>: nickname or topographic name derived from a Russian-influenced transliteration of <i>grushka</i> ‘pear, pear tree’."],"variants":[{"name":"Gray","meanings":["English, Scottish, and Irish (especially Eastern Ulster; of Norman origin): habitational name from Graye in Calvados, France, named from the Gallo-Roman personal name <i>Graec(i)us</i>, meaning ‘Greek’ + the locative suffix <i>-acum</i>. This is probably the chief source of the surname in Britain.","English: nickname for someone with gray hair or a gray beard, from Middle English <i>grey</i> (Old English <i>grǣg</i>, <i>grēg</i>) ‘gray’. In Ireland it has been used as a translation of various Gaelic surnames derived from <i>riabhach</i> ‘brindled, gray’, including <b>Mac Giolla Riabhaigh</b>; see   McGreevy  . In North America, this surname has assimilated names with similar meaning from other languages.","French: habitational name from Gray in Haute-Saône or Le Gray in Seine-Maritime."]},{"name":"Greiwe","meanings":["German: possibly a nickname from Middle High German <i>greibe</i> ‘sharp, tangy, dour’. Compare   Grey  ."]}]},{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes Grey was born about 1327. She married Henry De Aintree in 1288, in Aintree, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"Abt 1327–":"umbes 1327–Surnud","1225–Male":"1225–Surnud","1274–Female":"1274–Surnud","1327–Female":"1327–Surnud","1327":"1327","1225":"1225","1274":"1274","Abt 1327":"umbes 1327"},"fi":{"Abt 1327–":"noin 1327–Kuollut","1225–Male":"1225–Kuollut","1274–Female":"1274–Kuollut","1327–Female":"1327–Kuollut","1327":"1327","1225":"1225","1274":"1274","Abt 1327":"noin 1327"},"fr":{"Abt 1327–":"environ 1327–Décédée","1225–Male":"1225–Décédé","1274–Female":"1274–Décédée","1327–Female":"1327–Décédée","1327":"1327","1225":"1225","1274":"1274","Abt 1327":"environ 1327","lifeSummary":"Agnes Grey est née environ 1327. Elle a épousé Henry De Aintree en 1288, à Aintree, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"Abt 1327–":"um 1327–Verstorben","1225–Male":"1225–Verstorben","1274–Female":"1274–Verstorben","1327–Female":"1327–Verstorben","1327":"1327","1225":"1225","1274":"1274","Abt 1327":"um 1327","lifeSummary":"Agnes Grey wurde um 1327 geboren. Sie hat 1288 in Aintree, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom Henry De Aintree geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"Abt 1327–":"about 1327–Desede","1225–Male":"1225–Desede","1274–Female":"1274–Desede","1327–Female":"1327–Desede","1327":"1327","1225":"1225","1274":"1274","Abt 1327":"about 1327"},"hu":{"Abt 1327–":"1327 körül–elhunyt","1225–Male":"1225–elhunyt","1274–Female":"1274–elhunyt","1327–Female":"1327–elhunyt","1327":"1327","1225":"1225","1274":"1274","Abt 1327":"1327 körül"},"id":{"Abt 1327–":"sekitar 1327–Telah Meninggal","1225–Male":"1225–Telah Meninggal","1274–Female":"1274–Telah Meninggal","1327–Female":"1327–Telah Meninggal","1327":"1327","1225":"1